For anyone who wants to know:
His character has Tourette‚Äôs Syndrome. It is a neurological condition where the brain sends false or inappropriate signals to to the body. It means uncontrollable tics. I won‚Äôt say I know them all since I don‚Äôt. Everyone with Tourette‚Äôs is different and have different triggers. Mainly triggers come from nervous, anxious, excited, and any emotion except calmness. Talking about it to a person with it can sometimes trigger them. -Please no hate or saying I‚Äôm wrong because like I said it is different for everyone! I‚Äôm just going off on my personal experience with it and I love educating people over it! If anyone has questions feel free to ask!

I was diagnosed with Tourette Syndrome when I was 14. I very much approve of this, it is about time we got a movie like this. Started crying watching this trailer. As an adult sufferer of Tourettes, I have spent many years being ostracized, bullied, dismissed, and misunderstood. Up til now my media representation has been as the butt of a joke at best. I am so tired of hearing South Park and What About Bob references, and those tools were used to belittle and marginalize me growing up. Seeing this means the world to me. Seeing this means the world to future kids like me. Knowing that maybe the conversation surrounding this condition can change is so amazing. Christ, hearing a major actor with the same tics as me... god, that means everything. I will be seeing this movie. I hope you will, too.
